All Implemented Interfaces:
Connector
public class HibernateDBConnector
extends AbstractDBConnector

This Hibernate Connector uses the SettingsDAOHibernate.

Before the Data Access Object will be used, the SessionFactory will be injected into the DAO.

Author:
Harald.Brabenetz

Method Detail

setHibernateConfigXmlKeys

public void setHibernateConfigXmlKeys(String hibernateConfigXmlKeys)
You can set a customized hibernateConfigXml Key in your settings4j.xml
Default: "hibernate.cfg.xml"
You can set more than one File with the ',' Seperator
e.g.: "hibernate1.cfg.xml,hibernate2.cfg.xml"

The files will be readed by the given ContentResolvers. (default is ClasspathConntentResolver)

Example:
 <connector name="HibernateDBConnector" class="org.settings4j.connector.db.HibernateDBConnector">
     <param name="hibernateConfigXmlKeys" value="com/mycompany/myapp/hibernate.cfg.xml" />
     <contentResolver-ref ref="DefaultContentResolver" />
     <objectResolver-ref ref="DefaultObjectResolver" />
 </connector>

Parameters:
hibernateConfigXmlKeys - the comma seperated list of Hibernate-Configs.

setHibernateMappingXmlKeys

public void setHibernateMappingXmlKeys(String hibernateMappingXmlKeys)
You can set a customized HibernateMappingXml in your settings4j.xml
Default: "org/settings4j/connector/db/SettingsDTO.hbm.xml"

The files will be readed by the given ContentResolvers (default is ClasspathConntentResolver).

Example:
 <connector name="HibernateDBConnector" class="org.settings4j.connector.db.HibernateDBConnector">
     <param name="hibernateMappingXmlKeys" value="C:/CustomizedSettingsDTO.hbm.xml" />
     <contentResolver-ref ref="DefaultContentResolver" />
     <objectResolver-ref ref="DefaultObjectResolver" />
 </connector>

Parameters:
hibernateMappingXmlKeys - the comma seperated list of Hibernate-Mappings.

init

public void init()
This implementation creates a Hibernate SessionFactory an inject it into the settingsDAO. After this, the AbstractDBConnector.init() will be called to add this Object to the contentResolver list
